      "writtenOn": "2025-11-20T06:25:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we can use `.gn` because its interpretation might be ambigious.  For example, Chromium\u0027s `.gn` sets it to \"python3\":\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:.gn;l\u003d13;drc\u003dad4bc5ad2582b4bfd7c5ec2c7f6f6bc98077dadd\n\nThis is currently interpreted as \"look for python3 in the PATH\", *not* \"look for python3 inside the root dir\".  I think it\u0027s probably not feasible to change the interpretation in `.gn`.\n\nIn order to build chromium using python inside the root_dir, we need to instead use the `--script-executable` command-line switch, which is processed here:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/setup.cc#832\n\nUsing this switch, you can unambiguously specify the path to the python executable (whether inside or outside the root dir), and on Windows, the `ProcessFileExtensions` function will make it an absolute path.",
      "parentUuid": "b0798ee8_ee050d9e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 47,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 50,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "f0cdeb007fde05a2e173825d69273d905e1ee9a8",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
