      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think this will work for other platforms, because the logic that makes `python_path` an absolute path is *only performed on Windows*, see:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/setup.cc#793\n\nOn other platforms, python path is simply \"python3\" (e.g. in a non-Windows Chromium build).  So if we remove the `#if` here, then the `interpreter_path` in non-Windows builds would become `\u003cstartup_dir\u003e/python3`",
